b'Initially I was pretty intimidated to act with such powerhouses like @ViolaDavis & @Allisonbjanney in #TroopZero but these two only made me and everyone else feel comfortable. #TroopZeroTweetAlong https://t.co/2bqBMj7FMf'

b"It's very hot and humid in Louisiana where we shot #TroopZero.  To make things even warmer I wore polyester, a wig, and a cowboy hat.  Often after shooting I\xe2\x80\x99d take my wig off & hand it to a PA. Here is Fonzie  holding my wig after a hot day of shooting. #TroopZeroTweetAlong https://t.co/TAI82qHFBE"

b'My character Ramsey in #troopzero was always chewing on a toothbrush. It\xe2\x80\x99s in the script.  This meant I had to learn a southern Georgia accent and be able to do it with a toothbrush in my mouth.  Acting is strange but fun. #TroopZeroTweetAlong https://t.co/g4AdHhNib8'

b'When we shot this scene there was a professional alligator watcher because there were so many alligators around.  It made some #TroopZero cast members less than thrilled. There were plenty of stories from locals about pet dogs being eaten by gators. #TroopZeroTweetAlong https://t.co/GjcmCrKu8J'

b'Initially in this scene my character Ramsey was going to braid Christmas\xe2\x80\x99s hair.  Production gave me a wig to practice on at my hotel and in my trailer.  Eventually due to the timing of the scene I was directed to just \xe2\x80\x9cclean up/mat down\xe2\x80\x9d Christmas\xe2\x80\x99s messy hair. #TroopZero https://t.co/wobWYIXRbo'

b'The woman who plays the librarian was also our dialect coach #MaureenBrenan.  We were doing a South Georgia/North Florida accent where the screenwriter #LucyAlibar grew up. My character Ramsey was inspired by Lucy\xe2\x80\x99s father, a defense attorney. #TroopZeroTweetAlong https://t.co/R0fRluIPiE'

b'The delightfully talented #McKennaGrace who plays my daughter Christmas in #TroopZero, also played the daughter of @allisonbjanney in #ITonya.  Allison played my wife in #AwayWeGo.  There was an immediate familiarity on the set of #TroopZero. #TroopZeroTweetAlong'

b'Opening credits:  Juvee Productions is the production company of the great @Violadavis.  The main producer on #TroopZero was Todd Black who was like the papa bear of the production.  He\xe2\x80\x99s produced tons of great films. #TroopZeroTweetAlong'
